Hello Claude271,
To have gone through the state you describe (after a mix of chatterboxes, micropoints, taz, keta, finally everything that passed by there),  </s> To have gone through the state you describe (after a mix of chatterboxes, micropoints, Taz, Keta, finally everything that passed by there),
If I can give you advice, it's simply to tell you that all this is just psychological.
In general, the more you worry about these states, the worse they will get.
A very simple thing in such cases, you take deep breaths, you breathe softly, and you lie down in a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes sometimes you can have the impression that they are closing in on you).
After several months following a relapse, especially when you mix substances, you can experience effects, especially after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Claude532 said, consulting a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of the voices that are cluttering your head.
Keep the fish, and stay positive.
